How can I find my passion?
Adam Taha
Into developing leaders · Author has 5K answers and 94.4M answer views · Updated 6y ·

Yes, sure. I call it…

The Fuck You Program.

You’ll see why when you keep reading because you need the strong mindset of not giving a fuck especially when you fail and life throws it’s hooks at you…

Here is my Fuck You Program :)

I am now on the “Grow reach and website” phase, designing and building the website. I’m not going to hammer on free traffic as that’s slow. So been making money to invest in paid advertising to move heavy traffic when launched.

Also, I had to live first, solve the problems, which took years but also it came with lot of challenges as well but these were just obstacles I knew were to come and I had ideas to solve them and I did as they came.

That doesn’t mean I wasn’t working in a job.

I was a top earning sales rep, a marketing and editor chief of magazine for a company and I even became a teacher too.

I worked as a manager and various jobs because you have to also ensure you get the bills sorted but when the job was over on day, I switched off focusing on making my passion/lifestyle a reality.

I had to live first, gain lots of experiences and as I did, I changed as a man, my values changed and the path became clearer and specific on what my my passion is…

And it is what makes me..feel…alive.

So I still worked in jobs.

I worked different jobs but each one was not really for money but for a clear cut purpose.

I went for jobs to gain the experiences, specialised knowledge, skills and not the route of getting degree but hands on approach.

The jobs paid me good money to pay for the living, to invest in myself with knowledge, skills and being able to combine them all into a unique combination.

I will write the experience into a book one day

I first got to finish the phases, and I got tons of clients already, a team and when I can breathe, I will share the book on my new website.

So I am hoping it prepares you mentally, not to dishearten you but to toughen you for the journey ahead.

For now…

Here’s why I called it The Fuck You Program…

When passion is mentioned it seems to look like this..

But what it can look like the image below, when you find yourself alone as everyone says to you to be realistic, be like some else’s son or daughter.

You hear…

‘Why do you have to be so different and not follow same path as other brothers/sisters…or even the son/daughter of someone else…’

You will probably also hear parents saying they know better on what your life should be like….

You’ll hear how they did everything for you, how they sacrificed for you and on and on goes with the guilt trip as they tell you - to be normal and be realistic, and to just follow how everyone else does it.

It can make you feel like this…

It’s where you come from community of strict religion, culture, traditions and norms, where mostly everything you want to do, participate in and even achieve is forbidden.

That you will bring shame to the family and people will talk.

You could find yourself disowned, cast out, seen as shame and an embarrassment to the family…and…you now fear you won’t have the stability, financial support or the basics of a warm cozy home at your mummy’s and daddy’s basement.

You can also end up like this…for a long while or indefinitely…

I am not trying to cast doubts on your path nor trying to scare you from finding and following your ‘passion.’

But this needs to be said because so many believe this path is easy, predictable and most people procrastinate, do things to self sabotage because failure is predictable, it’s easy to do.

Even when doors open for people to get mentorship/coaching. Those doors close fast because the mentor has no time babysitting people who are not going to knuckle down and instead continue the old habits.

Most people who went on this journey found them in a dark place like there is no hope to make it happen but people don’t see what you had to do get to where you wanted to be but the finished product…

It’s easy to make every kind of excuses and it’s easy to do the self destructive talk, the lips to the internal self sabotage dialogue, instead of following the strategy and plan to get on with it as time is ticking.

It’s not passion you’re looking to find.

It’s the Purpose.

The case which come from a lot of living and facing your own demons and other people’s demons

It is the cause that drives you.

The reason why propelling you forward.

It’s like dating.

People over think, will read lots of books, read lots of blogs and do lots of other action except such as they so want to debate, give their fucking opinion but they are not doing the actions out in the real world that needs to be done.

It’s called a buffer…to procrastinate due to fear of rejection and success.

They don’t really believe in themselves. They do it to create predictable outcome, the victim story and the comfort zone is predictable.

There’s no one to push you and you either do it or you don’t.

No one wants to hear how hard it is or why you can’t get your shit together because everyone is trying to get their shit together.

I know I don’t want someone else’s program, listening day after day to that bullshit when I got rid of my own old DVD bullshit programs in my head.

No one is going to hold anyone’s hand because in the world where we hear people love winners and successful people, and all that “be yourself,” we find many won’t think twice to bring you down.

They want you to be the person they want you to be.

So this isn’t a journey for anyone who want to wait from inspiration and cheerleaders to get them off their ass.

It’s not for anyone who craves for validation, encouragement, cheerleaders appearing to get them moving when they procrastinate.

It is difficult for many people to believe in themselves.

Most are so excited in the beginning but then feel they are alone against the world. In between is the distractions of relationships, drama, and ongoing pursuit of wanting to be loved when the final mystery of love is self love..,

There is the battle with the self that needs a resolution.

It cannot be ignored anymore and it’s that which takes long.

Maybe you think it will happen in a year or five years but what if it is a path that takes a lot longer?

What then?

Do you really foresee at least the reality of the obstacles ahead?

You may think because you have found what makes you feel alive and you learn how to connect the dots to turn into money or to get a job but you may also find…you will have to stand on your own two feet as well at the same time.

On one hand you go your passion but in the other hand is reality, snapping at your ankles with bills to be paid, rent, food, surviving the debts.

You might think your closest, parents and friends to your teachers will be encouraging you to go for it.

But you find the story is very different.

This is the world I came from…

  1. You cannot date women.
  2. You cannot be alone with women
  3. You cannot have sex until you’re married
  4. You cannot draw people and also sexual erotic art
  5. You cannot sing using musical string instruments
  6. You are prohibited and if you do any of these, you will bring shame to the parents, and find yourself ostracized in the community.

So mostly everything I was passionate about was seen as going against the religion, beliefs, traditions, culture and norms.

That was one of the biggest obstacles.

For example…

I couldn’t show my creative work to my parents, friends, people in my community.

I combined my art, creative skills in painting, design, music, film and video product, writing to solve problems in dating, relationships, sex and nurturing relationships…

I had to learn different specialised skills. I had to take the money I earned from jobs to invest in learning these skills.

If anything wasn’t going to help with this goal, it was irrelevant to me and I didn’t waste my time on it.

Imagine, sitting down showing them hundreds of frames of your pencil animation which takes me a year to do one animated story, and it’s about different sex positions…

You can forget showing it.

Remember what I mentioned on how the community I come from follows religion, rules, customs, culture, sex is not talked about at all and seen as taboo if you do and nor is dating.

Even to the “modern” world, people are still going to bullshit you due to their own perceptions and where they are at in life.

You cannot show the many sketches and open a book showing your work…

You can’t open a page of one of your illustrations showing …

I couldn’t invite them to my exhibitions full of erotica paintings and see them watch as my work sells.

I couldn’t show them how I animate my work into a full blown movie story of how to increase sexual tension in relationship, to giving incredible blow jobs to eating pussy…

I couldn’t also give them a copy of my books I am writing and pages after pages illustrated, designed and that’s another skill I had to learn..

I couldn’t show the training videos..

I couldn’t even invite my parents, brothers and sisters to see me on stage in front of 10,000 people, with my band when singing, and all the gigs I did when touring.

So I couldn’t do for approval, for acceptance and to fit in.

I lived a double life.

In the day I was a top sales rep and I earned a lot of money. I also became a teacher. I also moved to other jobs, working with inventors to engineers and translating their concept into 3D animations.

I’ve worked taking sketches and making them into 3D physical products using 3D printers.

I worked as Editor in chief for magazine companies. I’ve been a copywriter for newspapers and other companies.

But….I wasn’t happy only when I went home, and had something to eat and hammered away doing the work I loved, burning both candles in creating my own world…

I had to keep all that locked down, secret.

My mum died not knowing and my dad, also the same.

Following your passion in the community and world I came from can be suicide.

Where I came from, following your passion especially in what makes me feel alive is seen as taboo or someone who wasn’t stable, a shame, a path in which only those without direct will follow.

Even in the world I am today, in England or even America, or if I fly to somewhere else in the modern world - there is social conditioning there too.

I came from a community, full of Islamic fundamentalist and much of what makes me feel alive was seen as evil, dark, a sin.

I couldn’t ask anyone I knew so I had to figure it out myself. I started by exploring all things I am into, to find out what made me feel alive.

Through the journey I learned numerous specialised knowledge and skills, to find that I felt alive solving problems and using art, writing, music, visual kind of communication and also digital.

But I still needed to be specific.

That’s the key..

  1. It makes you feel alive
  2. It needs to be specific
  3. It needs to focus on an industry/niche
  4. It needs to supply to a demand.

You’re going to have to see it as a journey because you need to explore and experience to figure out what it is you do that makes you feel alive, and then know how to connect all the dots to supply and demand.

This here took me years to get to….

Following your passion..

It can mean, no arab girl or any girl from such religious, strict, family upbringing and even those who are not, will marry you.

Most of all, if you believe in love but your nature is multiple relationships, well, most arab girls like most girls anywhere follow some princess story of..the soul mate…the one…and will always have this idea to find one guy to be accepted by family, friends, community and society.

Their fathers extreme, religious, strict and so, these young girls won’t get support to live their passion, their life, to grow, explore, make mistakes and if they make a mistake…their whole reputation is at stake.

They too, if they want to date a guy, they’ll do it secretly. If they want to follow their dreams, then they may have a fight on their hands.

You got young women who are told their role is to stay at home and pray. They cannot go abroad to learn and so they cannot get even get job experience, and life now is hell for them.

They face more than just dad, mum, sisters, brothers but the whole community packed with fundamentalist, the whole damn community, the lot of them are telling some guy and girl, that they know better because they are parents or religious clerics.

Everywhere you go, someone is trying to tell you how to live your life.

If these girls follow their passion…it is can be a huge risk because they could lose everything due to how it’s seen as going against their culture, going against their religion, their own people.

Now don’t get this wrong.

Not all parents and people in the community are like that but this happens a lot and it’s what I and many faced.

It’s same for a guy but not as bad as the guy can go out, when he wants more than the girls.

He will still be told..

“You don’t follow this, go for this or you are not our son! Don’t you date or marry out of the culture.”

Or if the guy wants to do something he feels strongly about, he hears these very words from everyone he knows…

“Be realistic.”

The fear for the guy is he will not get financial help for studies.

I wanted to paint you a picture of what following your passion can become. Everyone thinks they know better than you.

You think finding your passion will be it, the secret of all secrets but what most people don’t realise is most of the time the journey is paved with misery, heartache, loneliness, failure after failure, pain, battles after battles and you’re going to have to fight for all your worth.

Worse, you may find when you do achieve success…you cannot even share and show to those round you because….it’s a world far removed from theirs. It goes again their religious belief, culture, traditions…

You may have to do what so many of us had to do - go against your parents wishes, go against community perception, go against religious belief, say no to friends who try to exert some control with opinions.

You may even have to leave home, maybe even leave the country, the city the way I did and build a lifestyle as you leave everything behind.

What you do may not be easy for people to follow you because if they did follow, if they did comment, if they did vote, if they did share….they worry how it will look to their social peers.

Someone, somewhere is going to say you can’t do it, you haven't got it in you or whatever story they want you to believe.

This is why I called what I did “fuck you program” ;)

I didn’t do it to give to anyone. It was for me to figure out and apply.

But here’s the thing…

You might as well fight for the life you want to live and if you fail in that, it’s not as bad and worse, failing in something you’re heart was never into and living someone else’s expectations of what you suppose to become.

I’ve seen that road and I rather fail in doing what I am passionate about than on what my heart is not into and feel dead inside.

So take this…

Then figure it out.

I’ll see you on the other side of the storm.

Just walk in the eye of the storm. What’s the worse that can happen?

Fail?

Well, at least you fail on your own terms, by fighting your fight, not someone else’s battles or dreams or goals and empire.

Now that…is what success really is ;)
